lead_paragraph: Two California men arrested by the F.B.I. wanted to join the Islamic State group and bought a plane ticket for one of them to travel to Turkey, federal prosecutors said Friday.

headline.print_headline: California: Two Accused of Trying to Aid Terror
headline.main: California: Two Accused of Trying to Aid Terror

snippet: Two California men arrested by the F.B.I. wanted to join the Islamic State group and bought a plane ticket for one of them to travel to Turkey, federal prosecutors said Friday.
abstract: United States attorney's office charges California men Nader Elhuzayel and Muhanad Badawi with conspiring to provide aid to terrorist group; men bought plane ticket for Elhuzayel to go to Turkey to join Islamic State.
